author: Todderick Hunt | NJ Advance Media for NJ.com
title: Rutgers-Michigan State game visitors react to Saturday's clash
text:
Comments 
Multiple commitments and non-committed visitors attended Rutgers ' battle against Michigan State Saturday night. 
Some of the bigger names included NJ.com Top 50 members Rashan Gary, Corey Bowles and Drew Singleton of Paramus Catholic, and Old Tappan (N.J.) athlete Jordan Fuller. 
Calvert Hall (Towson, Md.) junior linebacker Tyshon Fogg also made the trip, and projects to become a national recruit, as well. 
Find out what they thought about the contest by clicking through the gallery above.
